Description:
No annotation on the envelope.
Envelope addressed to "Herrn Professor Dr. Evers Darmstadt Technische Hochschule Kunsthistor. Institut"

- Photocopies of reproductions of some paintings details (heads)
- Correspondence with Herbert and his wife T. Leyendecker dated 1951 and 1958
- Description of 'Girl, soldier and laughing old woman' attributed to Rubens
- Folder addressed to "Herrn Professor Dr. H. G. Evers Darmstadt Technische Hochschule Kunstgeschichtliches Institut" and dated 29.02.1952:
    - Photocopy of the reproduction of the 'Soldier, girl and laughing old woman'
    - Problems about the 'Soldier, girl and laughing old woman'
